INSERT INTO "submissions_dpquestion_2009" VALUES(10374,501,'2','2007','11326328.0','2009','17183301.0','2007: This includes £3.7m through the common fund, £11k TA and £2.5m Malaria project. 2009 includes £7m common fund, £243k TA and 2.4m Malaria project. DFID also provides GBS support, this was £36m in 2007 (of which 13% of govt budget went to health and £42m in 2009, of which 10% of govt budget went to health - however this funding has not been included in totals here. All GBS and Sector Budget Support is on budget and on plan. Malaria project funding is off budget, but registered on ODAMOZ the government system for recording project spend by sector. Using figures given here, 72% of funding is on budget. If GBS contribution to health were also included, over 85% of DFID support to health would be on budget. ');
